II.1. Existing blockchain technologies have limitations

All platform features, as well as the block generation process, 
require the use of the native token known as NXT.

NXT is not only required for the payment of transaction fees to 
the network and for the transfer of value, but also for all trans-
actions involving the use of the blockchain e.g. pricing of asset 
exchange ask/bid orders, prices of digital goods listed on the 
marketplace, exchange rates of monetary system currencies, 
and the transfer of assets over the blockchain. This makes it 
difficult to develop applications which use the blockchain 
transparently, as ideally, users should not be required to have 
NXT in order to transact and shouldn’t need to denominate the 
value of assets and currencies in NXT. 

Over the course of the development of Nxt, we identified a few problems 
that we needed to address. 

Single Token

Blockchain Bloat

Cloning Issues

a. Single Token

