Structure 

Function

Side chains are independent block-
chains that have a kind of "pegging 
mechanism", where at least one of the 
chains (main chain and side chain) is 
"aware" of the other chain and both 
tokens are pegged at a set ratio. Side 
chains need their own network secu-
rity and block processing.

Transactions executed between the 
locks and unlocks of the main chain 
tokens don't bloat the main chain. 
As the technology of a side chain is 
connected to its main chain, it can 
be used to build on the develop-
ments of the main chain and intro-
duce new features to the market.

"Child Chains" of the Ardor platform 
are tightly integrated into the main 
Ardor parent chain. All transactions 
are processed and secured by the 
parent chain forgers. This makes 
cross-chain transactions possible. 
Pruning will be enabled on child 
chain transactions in order to 
significantly reduce blockchain 
bloat by pruning the transactions on 
regular basis from the blockchain.

Child chains serve as the transac-
tional chains of the parent-child 
architecture, as the parent chain 
retains minimal features. 

III.6 Comparison between Side Chains and Child Chains

Side Chains Ardor Child Chains

We would like to emphasize that side chains and Ardor child chains are not the same. 
The differences are described below:

